HEADWORD: Systaltic
<hw>Sys*tal"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>systalticus</ets> drawing together, Gr. <?/, from <?/ to draw
together. Cf. <er>Sustaltic</er>, <er>Systole</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Capable of, or taking place by, alternate
contraction and dilatation; <as>as, the <ex>systaltic</ex> action of the
heart</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Systasis</ent>⟦br⟧
